<subSubSection id="1FE5655FFFE2416FCAD1ED0FFA842568" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="574036D4FFE2416FCAD1ED0FFD592418" blockId="20.[151,1436,1123,1294]" box="[151,747,1123,1149]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE2416FCAD1ED0FFE912418" bold="true" box="[151,291,1123,1149]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">References:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE2416FCB6CED0FFE7B2418" author="Schmidt, G. H." box="[298,457,1123,1149]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" pagination="121 - 137" refId="ref18582" refString="Schmidt, G. H. (1990) A new species of Gymnoproctus Karsch 1887 (Grylloptera, Tettigoniidae, Hetrodinae) from Kenya, with some notes on its biology. Tropical Zoology, 3, 121 - 137. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03946975.1990.10539456" type="journal article" year="1990">Schmidt 1990</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE2416FCB92ED0FFD592418" author="Schmidt, G. H. &amp; Mungai, M." box="[468,747,1123,1149]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" pagination="19 - 28" refId="ref18702" refString="Schmidt, G. H. &amp; Mungai, M. (1996) Notes on the distribution, variability and sexual behaviour of Gymnoproctus sculpturatus G. H. Schmidt, 1990, in Kenya-Tanzania (Grylloptera: Tettigonioidea: Hetrodidae). Bollettino del Laboratorio di Entomologia Agraria ' Filippo Silvestri', Portici, 51, 19 - 28." type="journal article" year="1996">Schmidt &amp; Mungai 1996</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="574036D4FFE2416FCA81EDEBFDC224A0" blockId="20.[151,1436,1123,1294]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE2416FCA81EDEBFED024C4" bold="true" box="[199,354,1159,1185]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Bioacoustics.</emphasis>
The calling song (
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE2416FC877EDEBFD3424C7" box="[561,646,1159,1186]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1776,1800]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,632,1736]" captionTargetId="figure-221@11.[151,1436,597,1753]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Oscillograms of the calling songs in the genera Acanthoplus, Gymnoproctus, Acanthoproctus and Hetrodes (figures of Acanthoplus, Acanthoproctus and Hetrodes based on figures and data from literature; see text). A Acanthoplus discoidalis, B–C Acanthoplus longipes, D Gymnoproctus rammei, E Gymnoproctus sculpturatus, F Gymnoproctus spec., G Acanthoproctus cervinus, H Acanthoproctus diadematus, I Hetrodes pupus. Left column overview (5-s-section), right column detail (250-mssection)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392729" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392729/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 7E</figureCitation>
) is quite similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="90FF4D57FFE2416FC9EDEDE4FB9124C4" authorityName="Weidner" authorityYear="1941" box="[939,1059,1160,1186]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Gymnoproctus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rammei">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE2416FC9EDEDE4FB9124C4" box="[939,1059,1160,1186]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">G. rammei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and consists of long series of syllables (song 
<typeStatus id="88448876FFE2416FCB63EDC0FEE724A3" box="[293,341,1196,1222]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">type</typeStatus>
B in 
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE2416FCBD4EDC7FE6424A3" box="[402,470,1195,1222]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1254,1278]" captionTargetBox="[158,1423,198,1221]" captionTargetId="figure-23@8.[151,1436,181,1231]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Oscillograms of song types in Hetrodini. Song consisting A of long trills (Cosmoderus femoralis CH8627), B of broken trills (including transitions to long echemes; B1 Spalacomimus talpa, B2 Enyaliopsis jennae, B3 Enyaliopsis ephippiatus) or C of regularly repeated echemes (C1 Spalacomimus spec. near verruciferus, C2 Eugaster guyoni). 1-min-sections." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392721/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
; see 
<tableCitation id="1A7D036FFFE2416FC84BEDC7FDD124A0" box="[525,611,1195,1221]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,236,476,501]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="TABLE 2. Song characteristics of Hetrodini species (for song type see Fig. 5 and text)" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/0380665CFFF1417CCAD1E8B0FBBD2190" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" tableUuid="0380665CFFF1417CCAD1E8B0FBBD2190">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="574036D4FFE2416FCA81EDA3FA842568" blockId="20.[151,1436,1123,1294]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE2416FCA81EDA3FE8F248C" bold="true" box="[199,317,1231,1257]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Genitalia.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE2416FCB9AEDA3FCB4248F" author="Schmidt, G. H. &amp; Mungai, M." box="[476,774,1231,1258]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" pagination="19 - 28" refId="ref18702" refString="Schmidt, G. H. &amp; Mungai, M. (1996) Notes on the distribution, variability and sexual behaviour of Gymnoproctus sculpturatus G. H. Schmidt, 1990, in Kenya-Tanzania (Grylloptera: Tettigonioidea: Hetrodidae). Bollettino del Laboratorio di Entomologia Agraria ' Filippo Silvestri', Portici, 51, 19 - 28." type="journal article" year="1996">Schmidt &amp; Mungai (1996)</bibRefCitation>
, the genitalic sclerites are only weakly sclerotized and easy to find in old males only. The titillator is triangular, broad in its base, and continuously tapering to the tip.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
